      \field{labeltitlesource}{title}
      \field{abstract}{Gematria, the interpretation of words with the help of the value of the letters, is the 32nd rule of the Tannaic Rabbi Eleazer. According to C. L. Labuschagne, the gematria of God's name Jhwh functions as a principle in the shaping of Old Testament texts. It also plays a role in the rabbinic and cabbalistic traditions. The article shows how the values 26, 17, and 39 are calculated, gives examples of where these numbers and multiples of 26 and 17 appear in the shaping of Old Testament texts, and explains what further associations exist due to gematria. The article then examines the number 72, which plays a role both in the shaping of Old Testament texts and in the oral Torah, and finally the number 186, which is only to be found in the oral Torah. Gematria is like a network of different arithmetics, with the help of which diverse associations come into being and so new meanings are generated.}
      \field{issn}{0010-3713}
      \field{journaltitle}{COMMUNIO VIATORUM}
      \field{number}{3}
      \field{title}{ABOUT THE GEMENTRY OF THE GOD'S NAME: YHWH IN THE HEBREW BIBLE, IN MIDRASCH AND IN THE MYSTIC - A SKETCH}
